title: Telephonies/Tough Love
description: Telephonies: The Gangreen Gang gets hold of the Powerpuff Girls' Hotline and makes crank calls sending the Powerpuff Girls on a wild goose chases all over town./Tough Love: Everyone in Townsville loves the Powerpuff Girls! But the citizens have a sudden change of heart when Him sends out an evil gas turning the entire town against their favorite superheroes.

title: Cat Man Do/Impeach Fuzz
description: Cat Man Do: Bubbles saves a seemingly innocent kitty from the clutches of an evil villain. But when the girls discover it's actually the Cat who is evil, they must save the Professor from being the next victim./Impeach Fuzz: When Fuzzy Lumkins throws his hat into the mayoral ring and claims a surprise victory, it's up to the Mayor and the girls to wrestle the office, and the Mayor's actual hat, back from him.

title: Princess Buttercup
description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

title: How to Draw Blossom
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Blossom.

title: Collect Her/Supper Villain
description: Collect Her: A fan of the Powerpuff Girls has collected every bit of Powerpuff stuff available, almost. His collection will be complete with three more items./Supper Villain: The girls' neighbor reveals he's not exactly the nice guy next door. But how will they capture him during a seemingly innocent dinner party?

title: Paste Makes Waste/Ice Sore
description: Paste Makes Waste: When Buttercup's taunting turns paste-eating classmate Elmer Sglue into a destructive Paste Monster, she gets out of a sticky situation by doing something against her tough nature, apologizing./Ice Sore: During a heat wave, Blossom discovers that she has a new power: ice breath. But when she doesn't use her new gift wisely, she gets a chilly reception from her sisters.

title: Bubbles' Beauty Blog But on Video
description: Bubbles' attempt to start her own beauty blog is thwarted by Blossom and Buttercup.

title: Air Buttercup
description: Buttercup tries to show off her basketball skills in the lunchroom to no avail.

title: Bubbs and Donny Get the Mail
description: Bubbles and Donny are given their most daring mission ever: get the mail.

title: Stuck Up, Up and Away/Schoolhouse Rocked
description: Stuck Up, Up and Away: Bratty little Princess comes to town and wants to be a Powerpuff Girl. When she doesn't get what she wants, the girls will have to pay./Schoolhouse Rocked: The Gangreen Gang goes back to school at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten and become the school bullies. Since the girls can't fight in school, how can they stop them?

title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

title: Escape from Monster Island
description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup.

title: Buttercrush/Fuzzy Logic
description: Buttercrush: Buttercup falls for Ace, the leader of the Gangreen Gang. But when the gang exploits her infatuation to lure Blossom and Bubbles into danger, Buttercup shows them the real meaning of the word crush./Fuzzy Logic: Beastly bumpkin Fuzzy Lumkins goes wild in Townsville and only the Powerpuff Girls, with some help from a flying squirrel, can teach him to respect other people's property.

title: Rock Off Battle Music Video
description: The Powerpuff Girls rock out!

title: Ping Pong Z
description: It's "loser does the dishes" when the girls play ping pong in and around Townsville.

title: Horn, Sweet Horn
description: Bubbles convinces the Professor to test his new transmogrifying ray on her new friend Donny the Pony in an effort to help him become the unicorn he's always wanted to be. But when it turns Donny into a monster instead, she must stop him before he destroys Townsville!

title: Checkin' Out!
description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

title: Painbow
description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

title: Brainlord
description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

title: The Rowdy Ruff Boys
description: Mojo Jojo creates the ultimate weapons against the Powerpuff Girls, boy equivalents! Enter Butch, Boomer and Brick, The Rowdyruff Boys.

title: Watch It!
description: The Powerpuff Girls are tasked with keeping a priceless gem safe from thieves.

title: Rebel Rebel
description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

title: Bedtime
description: The girls need to get a good night's rest before family photo day, but they just can't seem to fall asleep!

title: How to Draw Buttercup
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Buttercup.

title: Insect Inside/Powerpuff Bluff
description: Insect Inside: Vile villain Roach Coach has a plan to infest Townsville with an army of cockroaches! The girls overcome their squirms to squash Roach Coach's scheme and force him to bug off./Powerpuff Bluff: Three local hoods get new identities when they find grown-up-sized Powerpuff costumes inside Townsville Jail. They terrorize Townsville while the Mayor mistakenly sends the real girls to the slammer.

title: Man Up 4: The Donnyest Game
description: With Man-Boy on the loose, Donny must be prepared for anything.

title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom.

title: Sideline Dad
description: When the Girls start playing soccer, the Professor goes overboard.

title: Who's Got the Power?
description: Extended main title is set to music.

title: The Powerpuff Girls Movie
description: Blossom, Bubbles, and Buttercup--better known as the Powerpuff Girls--reveal the story of how they came to be the official protectors of the City of Townsville. When Professor Utonium first cooked up the Girls in his laboratory, he wasn't trying to give them superpowers. But when the Professor's mischievous monkey lab assistant Jojo knocked a dose of Chemical X into the mix, the Powerpuff Girls were born. While they have such powers as laser beam eyes, superhuman strength and the ability to fly at the speed of light, the Girls are only in Kindergarten. Although they don't mean to hurt anyone, their natural playfulness, coupled with their unnatural abilities, leads to some not-so-natural disasters and earns them the hatred of every man, woman and child in the city of Townsville. The girls are despondent, believing that their powers are evil and nobody loves them. Then Jojo slinks back onto the scene--but the Chemical X-plosion has mutated him into the evil genius Mojo Jojo. He convinces the Girls that he understands the pain of being an outsider, and lets them in on a plan that will endear them to all the people of Townsville--they will build a Help-the-Town-and-Make-it-a-Better-Place-Machine. The Girls immediately set to work gathering the necessary materials from all over the world. But what the Girls don't know is that Mojo Jojo has no intention of making Townsville a better place. In fact, he's planning on using the machine for his own nefarious purposes. Will the Girls realize the truth about Mojo as well as the true potential of their powers in time to really help the town and make it a better place?

title: I'll Be Bake
description: Bubbles and Buttercup's good intentions are bad news for the cake Blossom is trying to bake.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles.

title: Run, Blossom, Run
description: Blossom oversleeps and she'll stop at nothing to make it to school before she ruins her perfect attendance record!

title: The Oct-Father
description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

title: The Stayover
description: After going overboard on the candy, Blossom and Buttercup wake up with no memory of last night and no idea where Bubbles is! They must piece together the events of last night and find Bubbles before the Professor gets back!

title: How to Draw Bubbles
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Bubbles.

title: Mojo Builds a Shelf
description: Mojo discovers the only thing more difficult than total world domination is DIY furniture.

title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

title: Blissfully Unaware
description: Bliss uses her telekinetic powers to help the Professor make a more delicious dinner.

title: Drama Bomb
description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

title: Uh, Oh, Dynamo
description: Worried about his little girls' safety, the Professor creates Powerpuff Dynamo, a state-of-the-art protection system, to help them in battle.

title: Our Brand is Chaos
description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

title: Tagalong
description: Buttercup is tired of Bubbles following her everywhere.

title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.
